From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000010 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Petr Parkan Janda <petr.parkan.janda@oh-so.com>
Date: Sun, 22 Jun 2026 17:30:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] ARM: OMAP4: steelhead: SEV in prepare_cpus to wake CPU1 (stock parity)

On the OMAP4460 HS Nexus Q, enabling CONFIG_SMP silently deadlocks the whole
boot (no console/HDMI/network) when CPU1 is brought up. Reverse-engineering the
stock Android 3.0.8 SMP kernel (reverse-eng/vmlinux.bin) shows stock issues an
SEV inside platform_smp_prepare_cpus (dmb;dsb;sev;dsb @0xC001238C), immediately
after writing the CPU1 startup address to AUX_CORE_BOOT_1. Out of cold U-Boot
reset CPU1 is parked in ROM WFE; the ROM only (re)reads AUX_CORE_BOOT_1 after an
SEV wakes it, moving CPU1 into the kernel secondary hold loop. Mainline
omap4_smp_prepare_cpus omits this SEV and relies solely on the later SGI +
dsb_sev in omap4_boot_secondary, so on this bootloader CPU1 never leaves ROM WFE
and __cpu_up() blocks during smp_init, before any console -> the silent hang.

Mirror stock: add dsb_sev() at the end of omap4_smp_prepare_cpus, after the
AUX_CORE_BOOT_1 write. Applies on top of the SMP bring-up instrumentation patch.

Signed-off-by: Petr Parkan Janda <petr.parkan.janda@oh-so.com>
---
--- a/arch/arm/mach-omap2/omap-smp.c
+++ b/arch/arm/mach-omap2/omap-smp.c
@@ -413,6 +413,17 @@
 			       cfg.wakeupgen_base + OMAP_AUX_CORE_BOOT_1);
 
 	pr_emerg("STEELHEAD-SMP: prepare: AUX_CORE_BOOT1 startup addr written (0x%lx), prepare DONE\n", (unsigned long)__pa_symbol(cfg.startup_addr));
+
+	/*
+	 * Steelhead OMAP4460 HS: the stock kernel issues an SEV here, in
+	 * prepare, right after writing AUX_CORE_BOOT_1, to kick CPU1 out of
+	 * ROM WFE so it reads the startup address and enters the kernel hold
+	 * loop. Mainline omits this and relies on the later SGI + dsb_sev in
+	 * omap4_boot_secondary, which on a cold U-Boot boot leaves CPU1 parked
+	 * in ROM WFE -> silent SMP deadlock. Mirror stock (omap-smp.c @0xC001238C).
+	 */
+	pr_emerg("STEELHEAD-SMP: prepare: dsb_sev() to wake CPU1 from ROM WFE (stock-parity fix)\n");
+	dsb_sev();
 }
 
 const struct smp_operations omap4_smp_ops __initconst = {
